    "ts": "1738140555.845439",
    "client_msg_id": "19e3719c-8475-455e-a002-6ac8fb0ab1ab",
    "text": "AI-coding (chat) to create UIs — working software you can own — is the \"worse is better\" existential threat to traditional design tools and no-code.\n\nThis is as big, or bigger, than the \"worse is better\" that JavaScript pulled off for the Internet.\n\nChat is slow, but it gets the job done in a super accessible way, hence the \"worse is better\".\n\nThe real prize will be to combine the best parts of chat with the best parts of the canvas in design tools / no-code tools.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "yRCNy",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "AI-coding (chat) to create UIs — working software you can own — is the \"worse is better\" existential threat to traditional design tools and no-code.\n\nThis is as big, or bigger, than the \"worse is better\" that JavaScript pulled off for the Internet.\n\nChat is slow, but it gets the job done in a super accessible way, hence the \"worse is better\".\n\nThe real prize will be to combine the best parts of chat with the best parts of the canvas in design tools / no-code tools."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "thinking-together",
    "channel_id": "C5T9GPWFL"
  },
  {
    "user": "U08294YLWJH",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1738143719.650739",
    "client_msg_id": "6da814c0-a1ed-4fe8-a0fa-26b0158f44ba",
    "text": "I was sceptical about LLMs up till yesterday,\nwhat changed? - arrival of Deepseek R1\nDo I think it is \"Sputnik moment\" - not entirely,\nI think it is more like an \"Apple I moment\" - in a sence that now more people can experiment with this idea,\nAnd the tools are no longer in the hands of only big players.\nI will explore the combined approach - I will use LLM with some simple workflows,\nFor example verification/critique of answer first.\nAnd I will research the subject more carefully.\nI do not have powerfull hardware - Apple M1 and SteamDeck ,\nSo I hope that these limitations will benefit me.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "xy2/q",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I was sceptical about LLMs up till yesterday,\nwhat changed? - arrival of Deepseek R1\nDo I think it is \"Sputnik moment\" - not entirely,\nI think it is more like an \"Apple I moment\" - in a sence that now more people can experiment with this idea,\nAnd the tools are no longer in the hands of only big players.\nI will explore the combined approach - I will use LLM with some simple workflows,\nFor example verification/critique of answer first.\nAnd I will research the subject more carefully.\nI do not have powerfull hardware - Apple M1 and SteamDeck ,\nSo I hope that these limitations will benefit me."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "thinking-together",
    "channel_id": "C5T9GPWFL"
  },
